message_1:
Suppose a company has 5 employees and wants to form a committee of 3 members to attend a meeting. How many possible committees can the company form if:
1) all employees are eligible to be on the committee;
2) one employee is not available to be on the committee; 
3) two employees refuse to attend the meeting together and cannot be in the same committee? 

(Note: This problem can be solved using the concept of combinations and recurrence relations.)
